                title="Recommendations"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
              >
                
  
                <h2
                  class="title"
                >
                  
    
                  <a
                    id="recommendations"
                  />
                  Recommendations
                </h2>
                
  
                <div
                  class="panel panel--primary"
                >
                  
    
                  <p>
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="_Hlk41463321"
                    />
                    People have the right to be involved in discussions and make informed decisions about their care, as described in 
                    <a
                      class="link"
                      href="https://www.nice.org.uk/about/nice-communities/nice-and-the-public/making-decisions-about-your-care"
                      target="_top"
                    >
                      making decisions about your care
                    </a>
                    .
                  </p>
                  
    
                  <p>
                    
      
                    <a
                      class="link"
                      href="https://www.nice.org.uk/about/what-we-do/our-programmes/nice-guidance/nice-guidelines/making-decisions-using-nice-guidelines"
                      target="_top"
                    >
                      Making decisions using NICE guidelines
                    </a>
                     explains how we use words to show the strength (or certainty) of our recommendations, and has information about prescribing medicines (including off-label use), professional guidelines, standards and laws (including on consent and mental capacity), and safeguarding.
                  </p>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.1-referral-diagnosis-and-investigations"
                  title="1.1 Referral, diagnosis and investigations"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="referral-diagnosis-and-investigations"
                    />
                    1.1 Referral, diagnosis and investigations
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_referral-from-primary-care"
                    title="Referral from primary care"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="referral-from-primary-care"
                      />
                      Referral from primary care
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_1_1"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.1.1 
                        </span>
                        Refer for specialist opinion any adult with suspected persistent 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="recommendations"
                          data-original-url="#synovitis"
                          href="recommendations#synovitis"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          synovitis
                        </a>
                         of undetermined cause. Refer urgently (even with a normal acute-phase response, negative anti-cyclic citrullinated peptide [CCP] antibodies or rheumatoid factor) if any of the following apply:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              the small joints of the hands or feet are affected
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              more than one joint is affected
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              there has been a delay of 3Â months or longer between onset of symptoms and seeking medical advice. 
                              <strong>
                                [2009, amended 2018]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_investigations"
                    title="Investigations"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="investigations"
                      />
                      Investigations
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      If the following investigations are ordered in primary care, they should not delay referral for specialist opinion (see recommendation 1.1.1).
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="section"
                      id="ng100_investigations-for-diagnosis"
                      title="Investigations for diagnosis"
                    >
                      
        
                      <h5
                        class="title"
                      >
                        
          
                        <a
                          id="investigations-for-diagnosis"
                        />
                        Investigations for diagnosis
                      </h5>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="recommendation_text"
                        id="ng100_1_1_2"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p
                          class="numbered-paragraph"
                        >
                          
            
                          <span
                            class="paragraph-number"
                          >
                            1.1.2 
                          </span>
                          Offer to carry out a blood test for rheumatoid factor in adults with suspected rheumatoid arthritis (RA) who are found to have synovitis on clinical examination. 
                          <strong>
                            [2009]
                          </strong>
                        </p>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="recommendation_text"
                        id="ng100_1_1_3"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p
                          class="numbered-paragraph"
                        >
                          
            
                          <span
                            class="paragraph-number"
                          >
                            1.1.3 
                          </span>
                          Consider measuring anti-CCP antibodies in adults with suspected RA if they are negative for rheumatoid factor. 
                          <strong>
                            [2009, amended 2018]
                          </strong>
                        </p>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="recommendation_text"
                        id="ng100_1_1_4"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p
                          class="numbered-paragraph"
                        >
                          
            
                          <span
                            class="paragraph-number"
                          >
                            1.1.4 
                          </span>
                          X-ray the hands and feet in adults with suspected RA and persistent synovitis. 
                          <strong>
                            [2009, amended 2018]
                          </strong>
                        </p>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="section"
                      id="ng100_investigations-following-diagnosis"
                      title="Investigations following diagnosis"
                    >
                      
        
                      <h5
                        class="title"
                      >
                        
          
                        <a
                          id="investigations-following-diagnosis"
                        />
                        Investigations following diagnosis
                      </h5>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="recommendation_text"
                        id="ng100_1_1_5"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p
                          class="numbered-paragraph"
                        >
                          
            
                          <span
                            class="paragraph-number"
                          >
                            1.1.5 
                          </span>
                          As soon as possible after establishing a diagnosis of RA:
                        </p>
                        
          
                        <div
                          class="itemizedlist indented"
                        >
                          
            
                          <ul
                            class="itemizedlist"
                          >
                            
              
                            <li
                              class="listitem"
                            >
                              
                
                              <p>
                                measure anti-CCP antibodies, unless already measured to inform diagnosis 
                              </p>
                              
              
                            </li>
                            
              
                            <li
                              class="listitem"
                            >
                              
                
                              <p>
                                X-ray the hands and feet to establish whether erosions are present, unless X-rays were performed to inform diagnosis 
                              </p>
                              
              
                            </li>
                            
              
                            <li
                              class="listitem"
                            >
                              
                
                              <p>
                                measure functional ability using, for example, the Health Assessment Questionnaire (HAQ), to provide a baseline for assessing the functional response to treatment. 
                                <strong>
                                  [2018]
                                </strong>
                              </p>
                              
              
                            </li>
                            
            
                          </ul>
                          
          
                        </div>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="recommendation_text"
                        id="ng100_1_1_6"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p
                          class="numbered-paragraph"
                        >
                          
            
                          <span
                            class="paragraph-number"
                          >
                            1.1.6 
                          </span>
                          If anti-CCP antibodies are present or there are erosions on X-ray: 
                        </p>
                        
          
                        <div
                          class="itemizedlist indented"
                        >
                          
            
                          <ul
                            class="itemizedlist"
                          >
                            
              
                            <li
                              class="listitem"
                            >
                              
                
                              <p>
                                advise the person that they have an increased risk of radiological progression but not necessarily an increased risk of poor function, 
                                <strong>
                                  and
                                </strong>
                              </p>
                              
              
                            </li>
                            
              
                            <li
                              class="listitem"
                            >
                              
                
                              <p>
                                emphasise the importance of monitoring their condition, and seeking rapid access to specialist care if disease worsens or they have a flare. 
                                <strong>
                                  [2018]
                                </strong>
                              </p>
                              
              
                            </li>
                            
            
                          </ul>
                          
          
                        </div>
                        
          
                        <div
                          class="panel indented"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            
              
                            <a
                              id="_Hlk44061057"
                            />
                            For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see the 
                            <a
                              class="link"
                              data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                              data-original-url="#investigations-following-diagnosis-2"
                              href="rationale-and-impact#investigations-following-diagnosis-2"
                              rel="internal"
                              target="_top"
                            >
                              rationale and impact section on investigations following diagnosis
                            </a>
                            .
                          </p>
                          
            
                          <p>
                            Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                            <a
                              class="link"
                              href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-b-risk-factors-pdf-4903172319"
                              target="_top"
                            >
                              evidence review B: Risk factors
                            </a>
                            .
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </div>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.2-treattotarget-strategy"
                  title="1.2 Treat-to-target strategy"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="treat-to-target-strategy"
                    />
                    1.2 Treat-to-target strategy
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_2_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.2.1 
                      </span>
                      Treat active RA in adults with the aim of achieving a target of remission or low disease activity if remission cannot be achieved (
                      <a
                        class="link"
                        data-chapter="recommendations"
                        data-original-url="#treat-to-target"
                        href="recommendations#treat-to-target"
                        rel="internal"
                        target="_top"
                      >
                        treat-to-target
                      </a>
                      ). Achieving the target may involve trying multiple 
                      <a
                        class="link"
                        data-chapter="recommendations"
                        data-original-url="#conventional-disease-modifying-anti-rheumatic-drugs-cdmards"
                        href="recommendations#conventional-disease-modifying-anti-rheumatic-drugs-cdmards"
                        rel="internal"
                        target="_top"
                      >
                        conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs
                      </a>
                       (cDMARDs) and biological DMARDs with different mechanisms of action, one after the other. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018, amended 2020]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_2_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.2.2 
                      </span>
                      Consider making the target remission rather than low disease activity for people with an increased risk of radiological progression (presence of anti-CCP antibodies or erosions on X-ray at baseline assessment). 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_2_3"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.2.3 
                      </span>
                      In adults with active RA, measure C-reactive protein (CRP) and disease activity (using a composite score such as DAS28) monthly in specialist care until the target of remission or low disease activity is achieved. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="panel indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p>
                        For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see the 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                          data-original-url="#treat-to-target-strategy-2"
                          href="rationale-and-impact#treat-to-target-strategy-2"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          rationale and impact section on treat-to-target strategy
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <p>
                        Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-c-treattotarget-pdf-4903172320"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          evidence review C: Treat-to-target
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.3-communication-and-education"
                  title="1.3 Communication and education"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="communication-and-education"
                    />
                    1.3 Communication and education
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_3_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.3.1 
                      </span>
                      Explain the risks and benefits of treatment options to adults with RA in ways that can be easily understood. Throughout the course of their disease, offer them the opportunity to talk about and agree all aspects of their care, and respect the decisions they make. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_3_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.3.2 
                      </span>
                      Offer verbal and written information to adults with RA to:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            improve their understanding of the condition and its management, 
                            <strong>
                              and
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            counter any misconceptions they may have. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009
                            </strong>
                            ]
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_3_3"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.3.3 
                      </span>
                      Adults with RA who wish to know more about their disease and its management should be offered the opportunity to take part in existing educational activities, including self-management programmes. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.4-initial-pharmacological-management"
                  title="1.4 Initial pharmacological management"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="initial-pharmacological-management"
                    />
                    1.4 Initial pharmacological management
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_conventional-diseasemodifying-antirheumatic-drugs"
                    title="Conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="conventional-disease-modifying-anti-rheumatic-drugs"
                      />
                      Conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_4_1"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.4.1 
                        </span>
                        For adults with newly diagnosed active RA:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              Offer first-line treatment with cDMARD monotherapy using oral methotrexate, leflunomide or sulfasalazine as soon as possible and ideally within 3Â months of onset of persistent symptoms.
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              Consider hydroxychloroquine for first-line treatment as an alternative to oral methotrexate, leflunomide or sulfasalazine for mild or 
                              <a
                                class="link"
                                data-chapter="recommendations"
                                data-original-url="#palindromic"
                                href="recommendations#palindromic"
                                rel="internal"
                                target="_top"
                              >
                                palindromic
                              </a>
                               disease.
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              Escalate dose as tolerated. 
                              <strong>
                                [2018]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_4_2"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.4.2 
                        </span>
                        
          
                        <a
                          id="Short_term_bridging"
                        />
                        Consider short-term 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="recommendations"
                          data-original-url="#bridging-treatment"
                          href="recommendations#bridging-treatment"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          bridging treatment
                        </a>
                         with glucocorticoids (oral, intramuscular or intra-articular) when starting a new cDMARD. 
                        <strong>
                          [2018]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="panel indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p>
                          
            
                          <a
                            id="_Hlk83853224"
                          />
                          For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see the 
                          <a
                            class="link"
                            data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                            data-original-url="#short-term-bridging-treatment-with-glucocorticoids"
                            href="rationale-and-impact#short-term-bridging-treatment-with-glucocorticoids"
                            rel="internal"
                            target="_top"
                          >
                            rationale and impact section on short-term bridging treatment with glucocorticoids
                          </a>
                          .
                        </p>
                        
          
                        <p>
                          Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                          <a
                            class="link"
                            href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-h-glucocorticoids-pdf-4903172325"
                            target="_top"
                          >
                            evidence review H: Glucocorticoids
                          </a>
                          .
                        </p>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_4_3"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.4.3 
                        </span>
                        Offer additional cDMARDs (oral methotrexate, leflunomide, sulfasalazine or hydroxychloroquine) in combination in a 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="recommendations"
                          data-original-url="#step-up-strategy"
                          href="recommendations#step-up-strategy"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          step-up strategy
                        </a>
                         when the treatment target (remission or low disease activity) has not been achieved despite dose escalation. 
                        <strong>
                          [2018]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="panel indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <p>
                          For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see the 
                          <a
                            class="link"
                            data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                            data-original-url="#dmards"
                            href="rationale-and-impact#dmards"
                            rel="internal"
                            target="_top"
                          >
                            rationale and impact section on DMARDs
                          </a>
                          .
                        </p>
                        
          
                        <p>
                          Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                          <a
                            class="link"
                            href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-f-dmards-pdf-4903172323"
                            target="_top"
                          >
                            evidence review F: DMARDs
                          </a>
                          .
                        </p>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.5-further-pharmacological-management"
                  title="1.5 Further pharmacological management"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="further-pharmacological-management"
                    />
                    1.5 Further pharmacological management
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_biological-and-targeted-synthetic-dmards"
                    title="Biological and targeted synthetic DMARDs"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="biological-and-targeted-synthetic-dmards"
                      />
                      Biological and targeted synthetic DMARDs
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      NICE has published technology appraisal guidance on biological and targeted synthetic DMARDs for RA. For full details, see 
                      <a
                        class="link"
                        href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/conditions-and-diseases/musculoskeletal-conditions/arthritis/products?GuidanceProgramme=TA"
                        target="_top"
                      >
                        our topic page on arthritis
                      </a>
                      . For guidance on using DMARDs to achieve treatment targets, see 
                      <a
                        class="link"
                        data-chapter="recommendations"
                        data-original-url="#treat-to-target-strategy"
                        href="recommendations#treat-to-target-strategy"
                        rel="internal"
                        target="_top"
                      >
                        recommendation 1.2.1
                      </a>
                      .
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      The recommendations below are from NICE technology appraisal guidance 72. The 2009 guideline committee reviewed the evidence on anakinra and incorporated the recommendations into the guideline. The technology appraisal was then withdrawn.
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_5_1"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.5.1 
                        </span>
                        On the balance of its clinical benefits and cost effectiveness, anakinra is not recommended for the treatment of RA, except in the context of a controlled, long-term clinical study. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_5_2"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.5.2 
                        </span>
                        Patients currently receiving anakinra for RA may suffer loss of wellbeing if their treatment were discontinued at a time they did not anticipate. Therefore, patients should continue therapy with anakinra until they and their consultant consider it is appropriate to stop. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_5_3"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.5.3 
                        </span>
                        Do not offer the combination of tumour necrosis factor-Î± (TNF-Î±) inhibitor therapy and anakinra for RA. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_glucocorticoids"
                    title="Glucocorticoids"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="glucocorticoids"
                      />
                      Glucocorticoids
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_5_4"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.5.4 
                        </span>
                        Offer short-term treatment with glucocorticoids for managing flares in adults with recent-onset or established disease to rapidly decrease inflammation. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_5_5"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.5.5 
                        </span>
                        In adults with established RA, only continue long-term treatment with glucocorticoids when:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              the long-term complications of glucocorticoid therapy have been fully discussed, 
                              <strong>
                                and
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              all other treatment options (including biological and targeted synthetic DMARDs) have been offered. 
                              <strong>
                                [2009, amended 2018]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.6-symptom-control"
                  title="1.6 Symptom control"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="symptom-control"
                    />
                    1.6 Symptom control
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_6_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.6.1 
                      </span>
                      Consider oral non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs, including traditional NSAIDs and cox II selective inhibitors), when control of pain or stiffness is inadequate. Take account of potential gastrointestinal, liver and cardio-renal toxicity, and the person's risk factors, including age and pregnancy. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_6_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.6.2 
                      </span>
                      When treating symptoms of RA with oral NSAIDs:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            offer the lowest effective dose for the shortest possible time
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            offer a proton pump inhibitor (PPI), 
                            <strong>
                              and
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            review risk factors for adverse events regularly. 
                            <strong>
                              [2018]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_6_3"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.6.3 
                      </span>
                      If a person with RA needs to take low-dose aspirin, healthcare professionals should consider other treatments before adding an NSAID (with a PPI) if pain relief is ineffective or insufficient. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009, amended 2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="panel indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p>
                        For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see the 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                          data-original-url="#symptom-control-2"
                          href="rationale-and-impact#symptom-control-2"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          rationale and impact section on symptom control
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <p>
                        Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-g-analgesics-pdf-4903172324"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          evidence review G: Analgesics
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.7-the-multidisciplinary-team"
                  title="1.7 The multidisciplinary team"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="the-multidisciplinary-team"
                    />
                    1.7 The multidisciplinary team
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_7_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.7.1 
                      </span>
                      Adults with RA should have ongoing access to a multidisciplinary team. This should provide the opportunity for periodic assessments (see 1.9.2 and 1.9.3) of the effect of the disease on their lives (such as pain, fatigue, everyday activities, mobility, ability to work or take part in social or leisure activities, quality of life, mood, impact on sexual relationships) and help to manage the condition. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_7_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.7.2 
                      </span>
                      Adults with RA should have access to a named member of the multidisciplinary team (for example, the specialist nurse) who is responsible for coordinating their care. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.8-nonpharmacological-management"
                  title="1.8 Non-pharmacological management"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="non-pharmacological-management"
                    />
                    1.8 Non-pharmacological management
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_physiotherapy"
                    title="Physiotherapy"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="physiotherapy"
                      />
                      Physiotherapy
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_1"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.1 
                        </span>
                        Adults with RA should have access to specialist physiotherapy, with periodic review (see 1.9.2 and 1.9.3), to:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              improve general fitness and encourage regular exercise
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              learn exercises for enhancing joint flexibility, muscle strength and managing other functional impairments
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              learn about the short-term pain relief provided by methods such as transcutaneous electrical nerve stimulators (TENS) and wax baths. 
                              <strong>
                                [2009]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_occupational-therapy"
                    title="Occupational therapy"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="occupational-therapy"
                      />
                      Occupational therapy
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_2"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.2 
                        </span>
                        Adults with RA should have access to specialist occupational therapy, with periodic review (see 1.9.2 and 1.9.3), if they have:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              difficulties with any of their everyday activities, 
                              <strong>
                                or
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              problems with hand function. 
                              <strong>
                                [2009]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_hand-exercise-programmes"
                    title="Hand exercise programmes"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="hand-exercise-programmes"
                      />
                      Hand exercise programmes
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_3"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.3 
                        </span>
                        Consider a tailored strengthening and stretching hand exercise programme for adults with RA with pain and dysfunction of the hands or wrists if:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              they are not on a drug regimen for RA, 
                              <strong>
                                or
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              they have been on a stable drug regimen for RA for at least 3Â months. 
                              <strong>
                                [2015]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_4"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.4 
                        </span>
                        The tailored hand exercise programme for adults with RA should be delivered by a practitioner with training and skills in this area. 
                        <strong>
                          [2015]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_podiatry"
                    title="Podiatry"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="podiatry"
                      />
                      Podiatry
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_5"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.5 
                        </span>
                        All adults with RA and foot problems should have access to a podiatrist for assessment and periodic review of their foot health needs (see 1.9.2 and 1.9.3). 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_6"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.6 
                        </span>
                        Functional insoles and therapeutic footwear should be available for all adults with RA if indicated. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_psychological-interventions"
                    title="Psychological interventions"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="psychological-interventions"
                      />
                      Psychological interventions
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_7"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.7 
                        </span>
                        Offer psychological interventions (for example, relaxation, stress management and cognitive coping skills [such as managing negative thinking]) to help adults with RA adjust to living with their condition. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <p>
                        NICE has published a 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-original-url="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg91"
                          href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg91"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          guideline on depression in adults with a chronic physical health problem
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_diet-and-complementary-therapies"
                    title="Diet and complementary therapies"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="diet-and-complementary-therapies"
                      />
                      Diet and complementary therapies
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_8"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.8 
                        </span>
                        Inform adults with RA who wish to experiment with their diet that there is no strong evidence that their arthritis will benefit. However, they could be encouraged to follow the principles of a Mediterranean diet (more bread, fruit, vegetables and fish; less meat; and replace butter and cheese with products based on vegetable and plant oils). 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_9"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.9 
                        </span>
                        Inform adults with RA who wish to try complementary therapies that although some may provide short-term symptomatic benefit, there is little or no evidence for their long-term efficacy. 
                        <strong>
                          [2009]
                        </strong>
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="recommendation_text"
                      id="ng100_1_8_10"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p
                        class="numbered-paragraph"
                      >
                        
          
                        <span
                          class="paragraph-number"
                        >
                          1.8.10 
                        </span>
                        If an adult with RA decides to try complementary therapies, advise them:
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <div
                        class="itemizedlist indented"
                      >
                        
          
                        <ul
                          class="itemizedlist"
                        >
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              these approaches should not replace conventional treatment
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
            
                          <li
                            class="listitem"
                          >
                            
              
                            <p>
                              this should not prejudice the attitudes of members of the multidisciplinary team, or affect the care offered. 
                              <strong>
                                [2009]
                              </strong>
                            </p>
                            
            
                          </li>
                          
          
                        </ul>
                        
        
                      </div>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.9-monitoring"
                  title="1.9 Monitoring"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="monitoring"
                    />
                    1.9 Monitoring
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_9_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.9.1 
                      </span>
                      Ensure that all adults with RA have:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            rapid access to specialist care for flares
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            information about when and how to access specialist care, 
                            <strong>
                              and
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            ongoing drug monitoring. 
                            <strong>
                              [2018]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_9_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.9.2 
                      </span>
                      Consider a review appointment to take place 6Â months after achieving treatment target (remission or low disease activity) to ensure that the target has been maintained. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_9_3"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.9.3 
                      </span>
                      Offer all adults with RA, including those who have achieved the treatment target, an annual review to:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            assess disease activity and damage, and measure functional ability (using, for example, the Health Assessment Questionnaire [HAQ])
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            check for the development of comorbidities, such as hypertension, ischaemic heart disease, osteoporosis and depression
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            assess symptoms that suggest complications, such as vasculitis and disease of the cervical spine, lung or eyes
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            organise appropriate cross referral within the multidisciplinary team
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            assess the need for referral for surgery (see section 1.10)
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            assess the effect the disease is having on a person's life.
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            Follow 
                            <a
                              class="link"
                              data-chapter="recommendations"
                              data-original-url="#treat-to-target-strategy"
                              href="recommendations#treat-to-target-strategy"
                              rel="internal"
                              target="_top"
                            >
                              recommendation 1.2.1
                            </a>
                             if the target is not maintained. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009, amended 2020]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_9_4"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.9.4 
                      </span>
                      For adults who have maintained the treatment target (remission or low disease activity) for at least 1Â year without glucocorticoids, consider cautiously reducing drug doses or stopping drugs in a 
                      <a
                        class="link"
                        data-chapter="recommendations"
                        data-original-url="#step-down-strategy"
                        href="recommendations#step-down-strategy"
                        rel="internal"
                        target="_top"
                      >
                        step-down strategy
                      </a>
                      . Return promptly to the previous DMARD regimen if the treatment target is no longer met. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_9_5"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.9.5 
                      </span>
                      Do not use ultrasound for routine monitoring of disease activity in adults with RA. 
                      <strong>
                        [2018]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="panel indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <p>
                        
          
                        <a
                          id="_Hlk83853309"
                        />
                        For a short explanation of why the committee made the 2018 recommendations and how they might affect practice, see 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          data-chapter="rationale-and-impact"
                          data-original-url="#monitoring-2"
                          href="rationale-and-impact#monitoring-2"
                          rel="internal"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          rationale and impact section on monitoring
                        </a>
                        . 
                      </p>
                      
        
                      <p>
                        Full details of the evidence and the committee's discussion are in 
                        <a
                          class="link"
                          href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng100/evidence/evidence-review-e-frequency-of-monitoring-pdf-4903172322"
                          target="_top"
                        >
                          evidence review E: Frequency of monitoring
                        </a>
                        .
                      </p>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_1.10-timing-and-referral-for-surgery"
                  title="1.10 Timing and referral for surgery"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="timing-and-referral-for-surgery"
                    />
                    1.10 Timing and referral for surgery
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_1"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.1 
                      </span>
                      Offer to refer adults with RA for an early specialist surgical opinion if any of the following do not respond to optimal non-surgical management:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            persistent pain due to joint damage or other identifiable soft tissue cause
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            worsening joint function
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            progressive deformity
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            persistent localised synovitis. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_2"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.2 
                      </span>
                      Offer to refer adults with any of the following complications for a specialist surgical opinion before damage or deformity becomes irreversible:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            imminent or actual tendon rupture
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            nerve compression (for example, carpal tunnel syndrome)
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            stress fracture. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_3"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.3 
                      </span>
                      When surgery is offered to adults with RA, explain that the main expected benefits are:
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            pain relief
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            improvement, or prevention of further deterioration, of joint function, 
                            <strong>
                              and
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            prevention of deformity.
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            Cosmetic improvements should not be the dominant concern. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_4"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.4 
                      </span>
                      Offer urgent combined medical and surgical management to adults with RA who have suspected or proven septic arthritis (especially in a prosthetic joint). 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_5"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.5 
                      </span>
                      If an adult with RA develops any symptoms or signs that suggest cervical myelopathy (for example, paraesthesia, weakness, unsteadiness, reduced power, extensor plantars):
                    </p>
                    
      
                    <div
                      class="itemizedlist indented"
                    >
                      
        
                      <ul
                        class="itemizedlist"
                      >
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            request an urgent MRI scan, 
                            <strong>
                              and
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
          
                        <li
                          class="listitem"
                        >
                          
            
                          <p>
                            refer for a specialist surgical opinion. 
                            <strong>
                              [2009]
                            </strong>
                          </p>
                          
          
                        </li>
                        
        
                      </ul>
                      
      
                    </div>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="recommendation_text"
                    id="ng100_1_10_6"
                  >
                    
      
                    <p
                      class="numbered-paragraph"
                    >
                      
        
                      <span
                        class="paragraph-number"
                      >
                        1.10.6 
                      </span>
                      Do not let concerns about the long-term durability of prosthetic joints influence decisions to offer joint replacements to younger adults with RA. 
                      <strong>
                        [2009]
                      </strong>
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                
  
                <div
                  class="section"
                  id="ng100_terms-used-in-this-guideline"
                  title="Terms used in this guideline"
                >
                  
    
                  <h3
                    class="title"
                  >
                    
      
                    <a
                      id="terms-used-in-this-guideline"
                    />
                    Terms used in this guideline
                  </h3>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_bridging-treatment"
                    title="Bridging treatment"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="bridging-treatment"
                      />
                      Bridging treatment
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      Glucocorticoids used for a short period of time when a person is starting a new DMARD, intended to improve symptoms while waiting for the new DMARD to take effect (which can take 2 to 3Â months). 
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_conventional-diseasemodifying-antirheumatic-drugs-cdmards"
                    title="Conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs (cDMARDs)"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="conventional-disease-modifying-anti-rheumatic-drugs-cdmards"
                      />
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="_Conventional_disease_modifying"
                      />
                      Conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs (cDMARDs)
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      Conventional disease-modifying anti-rheumatic drugs are synthetic drugs that modify disease rather than just alleviating symptoms. They include methotrexate, sulfasalazine, leflunomide and hydroxychloroquine, but do not include biological DMARDs and targeted synthetic DMARDs. 
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_palindromic"
                    title="Palindromic"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="palindromic"
                      />
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="_Recommendation_1"
                      />
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="_Who_should_do"
                      />
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="_Step-down_strategy"
                      />
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="_Step-up_strategy"
                      />
                      Palindromic
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      Palindromic rheumatism is an inflammatory arthritis that causes attacks of joint pain and swelling similar to RA. Between attacks the joints return to normal.
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_stepup-strategy"
                    title="Step-up strategy"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="step-up-strategy"
                      />
                      Step-up strategy
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      Additional DMARDs are added to DMARD monotherapy when disease is not adequately controlled.
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_stepdown-strategy"
                    title="Step-down strategy"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="step-down-strategy"
                      />
                      Step-down strategy
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      During treatment with 2 or more DMARDs, tapering and stopping at least 1 drug once disease is adequately controlled.
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_synovitis"
                    title="Synovitis"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="synovitis"
                      />
                      Synovitis
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      Soft tissue joint swelling.
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
    
                  <div
                    class="section"
                    id="ng100_treattotarget"
                    title="Treat-to-target"
                  >
                    
      
                    <h4
                      class="title"
                    >
                      
        
                      <a
                        id="treat-to-target"
                      />
                      Treat-to-target
                    </h4>
                    
      
                    <p>
                      A treat-to-target strategy is a strategy that defines a treatment target (such as remission or low disease activity) and applies tight control (for example, monthly visits and respective treatment adjustment) to reach this target. The treatment strategy often follows a protocol for treatment adaptations depending on the disease activity level and degree of response to treatment.
                    </p>
                    
    
                  </div>
                  
  
                </div>
                

